  <section id="insurance-options">
    <h2>Insurance Options for Retirees</h2>
    <p>
      Hungary offers several healthcare coverage paths. Understanding international insurance, Hungarian private options, and the public system helps design appropriate protection.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>International health insurance</strong> is required for residence applications and provides comprehensive coverage including evacuation to major European centers when needed. For retirees wanting seamless access across Europe, international coverage remains the most flexible foundation.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Hungarian public healthcare (TB)</strong> is available to legal residents who contribute to the social insurance system. Coverage is comprehensive, though public facilities can involve waiting times and varying quality. Private insurance supplements public coverage for faster access and better facilities.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Hungarian private insurance</strong> from providers like Medicover and Generali offers local coverage with faster access to private facilities. Costs run €100-300/month for seniors. These provide good domestic coverage but limited international portability.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>European coverage coordination:</strong> EU citizens can use EHIC cards for temporary care across the EU. Non-EU residents with Hungarian coverage may have limited reciprocal access. International insurance provides clearer coverage across borders.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Combination strategies:</strong> Some retirees use Hungarian public/private coverage for routine local care while maintaining international insurance for complex care, evacuation, and European access. Given proximity to Vienna's excellent hospitals, evacuation coverage has real value.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="recommended-providers">
    <h2>Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
    <p>
      These international insurers provide comprehensive coverage for Hungary retirees with strong European networks and options for seniors over 65.
    </p>
    <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />
    <p>
      <strong>Cigna Global</strong> offers strong European coverage with established relationships in Hungary and neighboring countries. Their moratorium underwriting helps those with pre-existing conditions. They accept new members up to 74.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Allianz Care</strong> provides comprehensive European-focused plans with strong multilingual support. German-based operations provide efficient European administration. Good choice for those wanting Euro-denominated policies.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Bupa Global</strong> is strong for British expats with no maximum entry age for existing members. Their European network includes Hungary and provides seamless access to Vienna and other major centers when needed.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Aetna International</strong> offers unlimited evacuation coverage and comprehensive global plans. Their European operations support Hungary retirees who travel extensively throughout the EU.
    </p>
  </section>

